               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Introduction&#xD; - Canon tables (fols. 3v-6v) &#xD; - Letter of
                     Eusebius to Carpianus (fols. 7r-8r)&#xD; - The “Synopsis of Classes” (fols.
                     8va-9rb)&#xD; II) Gospel of Matthew (fols. 9va-49va)&#xD; - List of the
                     “tituli” for the Gospel of Matthew – 68 titles (fol. 9va-10rb)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta
                     Mātewos “Gospel of Matthew” (fols. 12ra-49va) &#xD; - Short postscript (fol.
                     49va)&#xD; III) Gospel of Mark (fols.49va-73va)&#xD; - List of the “tituli” for
                     the Gospel of Mark – 48 titles (fols. 49va-50ra)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta Mārqos “Gospel
                     of Mark” (fols. 51ra-73va)&#xD; - Short postscript (fol. 73va)&#xD; IV) Gospel
                     of Luke (fols. 73va-113ra)&#xD; - List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Luke –
                     84 titles (fols. 73va-74vb)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta Luqās “Gospel of Luke” (fols.
                     76ra-113ra)&#xD; - Short postscript (fol. 113ra)&#xD; V) Gospel of John
                     (fols.113ra-144vb)&#xD; - List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of John – 19
                     titles (fols. 113ra-113rb)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta Yoḥannǝs “Gospel of John” (fols.
                     114ra-144vb)&#xD; - Short postscript (fol. 144vb)&#xD; - Postscript for the
                     Four Gospels (fol. 144vb)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-11.</summary>
