                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning the arrival of monk Zabana Krǝstos at Dabra
                              Maʿṣo  Yoḥannǝs.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>:
                              በእንተ፡ ፍቅሩ፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ መጻእኩ፡ አነ፡ ዘባነ፡ ክርስ፡ ቶስ፡ መነኮስ፡ ሐነ፡
                              &lt;...&gt;፡ ለቤ፡ ተክርስቲያን፡ ኢትርስዑኒ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written by Zabana Krǝstos, a 17th-century monk and scribe, lived
                              during the time of Egyptian Patriarch Matthew and Ethiopian
                              Metropolitan Krǝstodulo (II) (in tenure 1664-71, d. 1675/76, s. EAE
                              IV, 441b). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#3ra">f. 3ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Note mentioning King Zarʾa Yāʿqob, by scribe Yoḥannǝs.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The note is the end of Additio 8. The beginning
                           and the main body of the note is on another leaf, which was misplaced
                           (after the conservation work, it returned on its place and is now <locus target="#3a">3a</locus>
                           <note>). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#3rb">f. 3rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on commemoration days of some individuals.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>: በእንተ፡ ዘከሮሙ፡ ለአበውየ፡ በሐለ፡ ሚካኤል፡
                              ዘሚካኤል፡ ለሀብተ፡ ሚካኤል። ተዝካሩ፡ አመ፲ወሰኑይ፡ ለሀምሌ።
                              ወተክለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወል፡ ዱ፡ ወተስፋ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ከማሆሙ፡ ኢተርስ፡ እዎሙ። ወሐብተ፡ ኢየሱስኒ፡ ተዘከሩ፡ አመ፡ ሀሙሱ፡ ለሐምሌ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of Zabana Krǝstos. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#7v">ff. 7v-8</locus>
                           <desc>v, 9rb: Prayer Fǝtḥat za-wald "Absolution of the Son".</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus from="7v" to="8v">7v-8v</locus>, 9rb: ፍትሐት፡ ዘወልድ፡ እግዚእ፡ እግኦ፡
                              ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድ፡ ዋሕድ፡ ቃለ፡ እግዚአብሔርአብ፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of Zabana Krǝstos in the bottom margins,
                              mentioning Egyptian Patriarch Matthew and Ethiopian Metropolitan
                              Krǝstodulo (II; 1664-71, d. 1675/76, s. EAE IV, 441b). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#10rb">f. 10rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Historiographic note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#10rb">10rb</locus>: በ፷፻፯፲ወ፮፡ አመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በ፫፻ወ፮፡ አመተ፡
                              ምሕረት፡ መጽአ፡ ርሀብ፡ ለዕለ፡ ኵሉ፡ ም[ድ]ር</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of Zabana Krǝstos (s. Nosnitsin 2011). The
                              note mentiones two dates. One is 6716 year of mercy, which is
                              difficult to interpret (it might be meant "from the creation of the
                              world", to correspond to 1224 A.D.). Another one is 316 year of mercy
                              which corresponds to 1664 A.D. (cp. Additio 6 in Ms. UM-027). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#10va">f. 10va</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on commemoration days of ʾƎndalu and his relatives.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">10va: በአኰቴታ፡ አብወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አነሀብተመርያም፡ ሐጥእ፡ ጸኀፍኩ፡ ለአቡይ። እንዳሉ፡
                              {ወለብእሲቱ፡ ዜነ፡ መርየም፡ ተዝከሮሙ፡ ምስለ፡ ብእሲሀ፡ በአኀዱ፡ ዕለት}
                              ተዝከረ፡ ዕረፍቱ፡ እም፳ወ፬ ለመስከረም፡ ወለዘ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወልዱሂ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ለሕዳር። ዕረፍቱ። ወለሰመረ፡
                              ክርስቶስሂ፡ ፳ወ፩። ለጥቅምት፡ ዕረፍቱሂ፡
                              ወቀተልዎ፡ እርብ፡ አረዕ፡ ወበጸሎቶሙ፡ ይምሐረኒ። ለኀጥእ፡ ሀብተመርያም፡ ለዐለም፡ ዐለም፡ አሜን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written by Habta Māryām (the hand is earlier than the hand of
                              Zabana Krǝstos). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#10va">f. 10va</locus>
                           <desc>-vb: Prayer, unidentified, possibly a later continuation of Additio
                              6.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#10va">10va-</locus>vb: ወዕቀቤሙ፡ በሃይ{ማ}ኖት፡ ርትዕት፡ ወያዕርጉ፡
                              ለከ፡ ስብሀት፡ ወከብር፡ በኵሉ፡ መዋዕለ፡ ሕይወ፡ ቶሙ፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of Zabana Krǝstos. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#11r">f. 11r</locus>
                           <desc>-v: Note commemorating Patriarch ʾAstona "za-hagärä Rome", who
                              resided and died on Dabra Maʿṣo.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written by the scribe Yoḥannǝs (s. Additio 2), in the time of King
                              Zarʾa Yāʿqob, on the order of Za-ʾAmanuʾel. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9">
                           <locus target="#50rb">f. 50rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Baʾǝnta ṣǝnʿa zatti makān... "For the strengthening of this
                              place..." (Litanic prayer).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#50rb">50rb</locus>: ወይብል፡ ካህን፡ ዘንተ፡ ስእለታት። በሳሙነ፡ ሕማማት።
                              በኵሉ፡ ሰዐታት፡ ወያወሥኡ፡ ሕዝብ፡ ወይብሉ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ተሠሃለነ። ጸልዩ። በእንተ፡ ዛቲ፡ ጽንዐ፡
                              መካን፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of the scribe Yoḥannǝs (s. above). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <locus target="#74rb">ff. 74rb-75</locus>
                           <desc>vb: Land charters of Dabra Maʿṣo.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the hand of scribe Walda Muse (19th cent.). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a11">
                           <locus target="#113v">f. 113v</locus>
                           <desc>: Recent  record concerning land possessions.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#113v">113v</locus>:  የርስት፡  ነገር፡  ሕንፃትን፡  ዘወልድን፡ 
                              አህዋት፡  ሕንፃት፡  ወልደ፡ ሚካዔል፡ ወልደ፡ ወልደሚካዔል፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in Tǝgrǝñña. </note>
                        </item>
